<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. valerieae" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="valerieae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">P. valerieae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique among the species described due to the presence of antero-admedian lines and for its dark mesoscutum, mesoscutellum, legs, and metasoma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Named in honor of the late Valerie Coughlan, a friend of Andrew Polaszek. The epithet is treated as a noun in the genitive case.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
